{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nPerform a read-only principal-engineer audit of rebar against modern software architecture and open-source community standards. Examine README.md, pyproject.toml, src/rebar/, tests/, docs/architecture.md, docs/adr/, CI workflows, packaging metadata, security posture, extension contracts, and contributor governance.\n\n## Plan\n- Map subsystem boundaries, dependency direction, data ownership, public APIs, CLI/MCP adapters, and the git-backed event store.\n- Inspect tests, CI, release/packaging, security, documentation, accessibility of contribution, and project governance.\n- Ground material findings in exact repository evidence and distinguish strengths, risks, and tradeoffs.\n- Produce a prioritized remediation roadmap without modifying production code.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The audit explains the architecture and identifies evidence-backed strengths.\n- [ ] Each material risk is assigned a clear severity.\n- [ ] Each material risk includes concrete code or documentation citations.\n- [ ] The assessment covers OSS baseline artifacts, packaging, CI, security, governance, contributor experience, testing, and operability.\n- [ ] Recommendations distinguish near-term fixes from longer-term architectural investments.\n- [ ] Audit observations and final conclusions are recorded on this ticket."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784138593625040001,"uuid":"178597c7-132c-4eba-9a27-854de0b30281"}